In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims October 2018 as National Substance Abuse Prevention Month. He recognizes the importance of ending and preventing substance abuse and emphasizes the need to raise awareness about the harms of alcohol, drugs, and prescription opioids. The article mentions the opioid epidemic and the devastating effects it has had on the country, including overdose fatalities and the impact on families. The administration has launched public awareness campaigns and awarded funding to prevent youth drug abuse. The president calls on various individuals and organizations to support evidence-based prevention programs and engage in activities to promote substance abuse prevention efforts in their communities.